The paper proposes a neural network model for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The model also involves capsule layers, which are a relatively new concept in deep learning, and the paper proposes a novel approach to using them for segmentation. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The paper also involves a recursive, layer-by-layer procedure, which could be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques, such as modeling the procedure as a traceback pipeline, which could be relevant to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category.
